      <h1 class="title" id="page-title">
       How to Plan a Wedding in Five Months or Less!
      </h1>
      <article about="/blog/wedding-insider/plan-a-wedding-in-5-months-or-less.html" class="node-693 node node-blog view-mode-full clearfix" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">
       <header>
        <span class="rdf-meta element-hidden" content="How to Plan a Wedding in Five Months or Less!" property="dc:title">
        </span>
       </header>
       <span class="a2a_kit a2a_target addtoany_list" id="da2a_1">
        <div class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 a2a_default_style">
         <a class="a2a_button_facebook">
         </a>
         <a class="a2a_button_twitter">
         </a>
         <a class="a2a_button_google_plus">
         </a>
         <a class="a2a_button_pinterest">
         </a>
         <a class="a2a_button_linkedin">
         </a>
         <a class="a2a_dd" href="http://www.addtoany.com/share_save">
         </a>
        </div>
        <script src="http://static.addtoany.com/menu/page.js" type="text/javascript">
         &lt;/scrip
      &lt;a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share_save" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share_save#url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.countryclubreceptions.com%2Fblog%2Fwedding-insider%2Fplan-a-wedding-in-5-months-or-less.html&amp;title=How%20to%20Plan%20a%20Wedding%20in%20Five%20Months%20or%20Less%21"&gt;&lt;img src="/sites/all/modules/contrib/addtoany/images/share_save_171_16.png" width="171" height="16" alt="Share"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
      
    &lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;
&lt;!--//--&gt;&lt;![CDATA[//&gt;&lt;!--
da2a.script_load();
//--&gt;&lt;!]]&gt;
        </script>
        <div class="field field-name-field-blog-author field-type-text field-label-hidden">
         <div class="field-items">
          <div class="field-item even">
           AGC Blogs
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="field field-name-field-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden">
         <div class="field-items">
          <div class="field-item even">
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             Wedding planning is a very exciting time! Although the average booking cycle is 12 to 18 months, your needs might be different and you'll want to wed sooner. Read on for some tips on how to plan a wedding in five months or less.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              1) Decide Must-Haves
             </strong>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             Now that the wedding industry has grown so rapidly in recent years, planning for one can be somewhat overwhelming. Although new trends are popping up all the time, its important to realize youre only one personand not every fabulous idea is one youll want to pursue.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             One advantage to a shorter planning period is that theres less likelihood youll change ideas midstream. Deciding early on your must-haves is a great place to start.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              <img alt="" height="203" src="data:image/png;base64," style="float: left;" width="243"/>
              2) Get Organized
             </strong>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             To enure no detail is overlooked, create a bridal planning binder to gather ideas and checklists in one place. You can also sign up for an electronic version at
             <a href="http://www.theknot.com/?MsdVisit=1">
              The Knot
             </a>
             or similar websites. Having everything in one place will not only help you stay organized, itll also keep you aware of details you might otherwise miss, such as boutonnieres, ceremony music, the rehearsal dinner, bridal shower, and more!
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              3) Book Your Venue First
             </strong>
            </span>
            <img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," style="float: right;"/>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             Once you've reserved your venue, you can then start planning the rest of the day. Because your planning period is shorter than so
            </span>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             me,
            </span>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             it can be helpful to select a venue that offers all-inclusive packages.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             For example, a golf course or country club venue offers food preparation and service, tables, chairs, linens, set up, staffing, and someone to aid in the event organization. Because these venues host several events like this, they'll also help guide you through the planning process by offering suggestions and answering questions, thereby greatly reducing the amount of work youll need to do.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              4) Choose Attire
             </strong>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             Because the right bridal gown can take some time to pick outand alterations are often neededits a good idea to order yours as soon as possible. Make sure to allow six weeks for the dress to ship to a local store, if need be.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             At the same time, you should also start reviewing bridesmaid, groom, and groomsmen attire. Although they wont take as long as your gown to come in, youll want to give yourself plenty of time to choose a style and color best suited to your ceremonyas well as any accessories you want to accompany them.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              5) Book Vendors
             </strong>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             One advantage to planning a wedding in five months is that any available vendors will clamor for your business, putting you in a great position to negotiate. Make sure you meet with a few in each category to compare, and the ones youll most likely need are a photographer, DJ/and or emcee, florist, wedding officiate, and hair and make-up artist.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             Plan ahead and bring pictures and ideas to meetingsand dont be afraid request references, samples, or portfolios. Inform them of your budget, and see if theyre able to offer a customized package within your parameters.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              <img alt="" src="data:image/png;base64," style="float: left;"/>
              6) Define your Style
             </strong>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             Images taken from magazines and the web are a great place to start brainstorming your weddings overall style. Helpful websites are
             <a href="http://www.theknot.com/?MsdVisit=1">
              The Knot
             </a>
             ,
             <a href="http://www.weddingwire.com/">
              WeddingWire
             </a>
             ,
             <a href="http://pinterest.com/">
              Pinterest
             </a>
             , and
             <a href="http://www.google.com/imghp">
              Google Images
             </a>
             . Combine several images you like in each category and add them to your bridal binder; vendors can take favorite aspects of each idea and create exactly what youre looking for. Soon enough, youll start to hone in on a style unique to you and your fianc!
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <strong>
              7) Designate Helpers
             </strong>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             If your budget doesn't allow for a wedding coordinator, its important to delegate responsibilities so the day goes off without a hitch. Start with members of your bridal partythey can help put together your favors and decorations. Throw a cocktail party to make it fun and invite the groomsmen, too; this will also help your bridal party to get to know each other better.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             For much-needed assistance on the big day, assign close friends and family members various tasks, such as manning the entrance table; setting out place cards, favors, custom champagne and cutlery sets, and the guestbook; and most importantly, coordinating with vendors to make sure all is set up as planned. Chances are theyll not only be glad to help, theyll have fun doing it!
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
             <a href="http://countryclubreceptions.com/the-wedding-insider/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/8.jpg">
              <br/>
             </a>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
            <span style="font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: medium;">
            </span>
           </p>
           <p>
           </p>
          </div>
